ZH: 这只螃蟹有一个硬壳。
EN: This crab has a hard shell.

ZH: 海龟的壳可以保护它们。
EN: The turtles' shells can protect them.

ZH: 她用壳做了一副漂亮的耳环。
EN: She made a beautiful pair of earrings out of shells.

ZH: 那条龙虾有一个坚硬的外壳。
EN: That lobster has a hard outer shell.

ZH: 壳可以保护动物的身体。
EN: Shells can protect animals' bodies.

ZH: 我们用壳做了一个壁灯。
EN: We made a wall lamp out of shells.

ZH: 海星的外壳光滑而闪亮。
EN: The starfish's shell is smooth and shiny.

ZH: 他收集各种各样的美丽贝壳。
EN: He collects all kinds of beautiful shells.

ZH: 这个海滩上有许多小虾壳。
EN: There are many small shrimp shells on this beach.

ZH: 海洋生物依靠壳来保护自己。
EN: Marine animals rely on shells to protect themselves.

ZH: 我们在海滩上发现了一个完好无损的大贝壳。
EN: We found a perfectly intact large shell on the beach.

ZH: 松树枝下铺满了坚硬的松果壳。
EN: The ground under the pine tree is covered with hard pine cone shells.

ZH: 壳的颜色和形状各不相同。
EN: Shells come in different colors and shapes.

ZH: 海螺壳的纹路很美。
EN: The patterns on conch shells are beautiful.

ZH: 螺蛳的壳有条纹。
EN: Snail shells have stripes.

ZH: 这只螃蟹重新长出一只壳。
EN: This crab has grown a new shell.

ZH: 壳是许多动物身体的一部分。
EN: Shells are a part of many animals' bodies.

ZH: 海胆的壳坚硬且坚固。
EN: Sea urchins' shells are hard and sturdy.

ZH: 这个海洋生物的壳非常美丽。
EN: The shell of this marine creature is very beautiful.

ZH: 她的手镯上镶嵌了许多小贝壳。
EN: Her bracelet is inlaid with many small shells.
